thread.text:
@raqball - Glad to hear you like the phone so far. I know you were on the fence since launch and it sounds like the wait was worth it.
Performance on the November update has been excellent. It keeps getting smoother with each OTA.
And, you're right about the camera. I've been using the Essential camera app far more lately and uninstalled the Google HDR+ port. I'm getting better daytime results from the stock app.

@bhatech Keep in mind that we'll always hear the worst of the worst complaints online. Those who are happy with their devices will rarely join a forum to say how happy they are with their stuff. Forums are where people go for help, advice and to vent about negative experiences. So, using the feedback here can quickly color one's judgment to think that there's a 100% defect rate and the company will be belly-up by tomorrow morning.
Did anyone think One Plus would survive this long? Probably not at the time.
Regarding the Sept update, no, nothing here. Most reviewers received engineering samples so it's possible that their IMEI numbers were flagged to get updates first to try and mitigate even more negative reviews. Hopefully we see it soon. I believe Essential claimed security patches on devices purchased direct would drop OTA within two weeks of their release date from Google.

@bhatech I suspect the camera will be a major focus going forward. They made a huge deal about the mono/color combo online, bragged about the engineers behind it, etc. The initial photos looked good but reviewers haven't been able to produce similar results.
@1901Madison Yes, it's certainly possible this phone might suck for some people and in some ways. Build quality doesn't seem to be one of the complaints. Photo quality will hopefully improve with time. The question might come down to confidence in the brand overall. If they don't make some PR magic happen and set customers' minds at ease, they'll see a heavy return rate in the 15-day period purely because some won't want to (or can't afford to) take a $699 risk.
As I've always said, I'm giving it a fair chance and rely on my own review. But, if it sucks then it will get returned. The problem then will be in finding an alternative and I don't see anything built or designed remotely close to this.
